It is in degree that differences can be recognised: degrees of intensity, complexity, and frequency. \n\xa0\nBecause of this greater intensity, the reflective space required to process complex emotional difficulties is rarely available to families living in areas of high deprivation\xa0or to\xa0other families\xa0whose children have additional needs.\xa0 Recognising this, we create a safe, nurturing environment and offer opportunities to reflect, to sort out, to reduce reactivity and to clear space for rational choice.\xa0 As a result, parents become a resource to their children  who then find space to learn.\xa0 Behaviour improves, school attendance rises and children are happier.\xa0 In enabling communities to develop among families who are often isolated, our work also opens parents as a resource to each other and their relationship with the school improves.\xa0 Everyone benefits.Our proven services take a holistic approach involving children, parents, school staff and our therapists.\xa0 Together, we identify and break through cycles which may have been repeated from generation to generation.\nTo achieve our goals and to operate effectively, we need to collect a certain amount of personal information from schools, families, supporters, staff, volunteers and trustees.\xa0 For details of our approach to safeguarding this personal information, please see our privacy statement.\n\xa0\n\xa0\n\xa0\n\n\xa0\nIf you are a parent or guardian looking for further information about Family Group, please visit our Family Group website www.sfwfamilygroup.org\n\xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0\n\n\n\n